He's still laughing wildly, madly.

169
00:20:21,059 --> 00:20:26,420
Puts Him in a bathtub, like up to His neck,
in the same liquid. He's splashing around,

170
00:20:26,420 --> 00:20:33,750
laughing madly. Śrīvās Ṭhākur of the
Pañca-tattva comes to visit. And, she's going,

171
00:20:33,750 --> 00:20:39,660
“Śrīvās —Nimaī lost His mind.”And,
he... what does he say to her, “I want a

172
00:20:39,660 --> 00:20:47,850
drop of what He's got. [laughing] Give me
a drop of that Divine substance.” And, then

173
00:20:47,850 --> 00:20:53,540
He stops laughing. He said, “Śrīvās,
if you thought I was crazy, then I would just

174
00:20:53,540 --> 00:20:58,679
leave the world. What's the point. But, that
you understand, that gives me some hope.”

175
00:20:58,679 --> 00:21:04,830
So, the devotees know. But, the non-devotees,
who He has come to liberate, they do not know.

176
00:21:04,830 --> 00:21:14,060
And, in Guru Mahārāj's words, “The patient
is abusing the doctor.” The doctor's, like,

177
00:21:14,060 --> 00:21:23,929
trying to give the medicine, and the patient
is refusing. And, abusing that very doctor

178
00:21:23,929 --> 00:21:26,430
who's come to rescue them.

179
00:21:26,430 --> 00:21:42,130
So, He devises a strategy for this campaign,
that, if I take sannyās —the custom is

180
00:21:42,130 --> 00:21:48,340
such, that everyone will have to show me regard.
They'll have to respect me. And, we know,

181
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:53,100
as Guru Mahārāj says, “When you accumulate
—that'll means, you'll accumulate sukṛti—

182
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:59,700
with the accumulation of sukṛti. You'll
acquire the capacity for appreciation.”

183
00:21:59,700 --> 00:22:07,820
That's important to understand. The accumulation
of sukṛti results in acquired capacity for

184
00:22:07,820 --> 00:22:13,910
appreciation. That's how you can appreciate
Kṛṣṇa Consciousness. Because, it's beyond

185
00:22:13,910 --> 00:22:27,290
rational. So, He internally reaches this decision.
Remember, His wife is 14.

186
00:22:27,290 --> 00:22:35,990
This is still Vedic culture. She's 14. Viṣṇu
Priya devī is 14 years old. And, His eldest

187
00:22:35,990 --> 00:22:41,990
brother Viśvarūp, he already took sannyās,
and father's left the world. So, Mother Śacī,

188
00:22:41,990 --> 00:22:49,270
she's under the care of Him. So, He's taking
care of His wife and His mother. So, to take

189
00:22:49,270 --> 00:22:58,580
sannyās means He'll have to leave them. And,
I mean, this would be heartbreaking in a normal

190
00:22:58,580 --> 00:23:07,220
circumstance. But... what to say... We can't
conceive the sort of love that Mother Śacī

191
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:13,100
has for Nimaī. So, if you can understand
how you... we think that we love people in

192
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:23,350
this world, you know, our partners, or children,
or parents, or whatever it might be.

193
00:23:23,350 --> 00:23:34,880
If we amplify that, multiply that —ad infinitum,
then what's... how much maternal love could

194
00:23:34,880 --> 00:23:43,290
Śacī-mātā have for Nimaī; Yaśodā for
Kṛṣṇa. Just as Guru Mahārāj said,

195
00:23:43,290 --> 00:23:53,380
when we talk about, sevonmukhe hi jihvādau,
svayam eva sphuraty adaḥ (Cc: Madhya-līlla,

196
00:23:53,380 --> 00:24:02,840
17.136.3-4) —the current. Current... devotional
current of the... the voltage of the devotional

197
00:24:02,840 --> 00:24:10,230
current of the kṛṣṇa-nām of Yaśodā
when she takes Kṛṣṇa's name. The voltage

198
00:24:10,230 --> 00:24:17,730
of the loving devotional current in the kṛṣṇa-nām
of Śrīmatī Rādhārāṇi. What is it like,

199
00:24:17,730 --> 00:24:27,070
when she takes Kṛṣṇa's name? What affect
does that have upon Him? They're inseparable.

200
00:24:27,070 --> 00:24:33,620
How can... how... it's heartbreaking for the
devotees. What the... the devotees, they can't

201
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:40,640
imagine what this will do to Śacī-mātā
and Viṣṇu Priya. It's killing them. Advaita

202
00:24:40,640 --> 00:24:47,070
Ācārya threatens suicide. And, —saying
that— what he thinks, “If I try to do

203
00:24:47,070 --> 00:24:54,299
it in the day, the devotees will stop me.
So, I'm just going to maintain my composure

204
00:24:54,299 --> 00:25:01,820
during the day; tonight I'll finish myself.”
They're like that. So, He... Nimaī Paṇḍit,

205
00:25:01,820 --> 00:25:09,990
before He meets with Nityānanda Prabhu, only
a few know what He's going to do. And, of

206
00:25:09,990 --> 00:25:15,210
course, Nityānanda knows these pastimes,
but... That's where we... it's hard for us

207
00:25:15,210 --> 00:25:24,050
to conceive because, on the one hand, we know
it's like a play. It's līlā, these are pastimes.

208
00:25:24,050 --> 00:25:30,510
But, by the grace of the Goswāmīs, we're
given some insight. So, we know, that Yoga-māyā,

209
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:41,539
her... one of her functions is to create spiritual
illusion, by which, this is all perceived

210
00:25:41,539 --> 00:25:53,660
to be real. And, that allows them to experience
the greatest depths of emotionality. Because,

211
00:25:53,660 --> 00:26:04,730
we'll think, “Well, they must know, I mean,
that there will be a happy ending.” No,

212
00:26:04,730 --> 00:26:10,730
even in this... look in our own experience.
The Stanislavski Method... Those actors act...

213
00:26:10,730 --> 00:26:17,990
they go so deep into the part, they're lost
in that character. That's the Stanislavski

214
00:26:17,990 --> 00:26:24,000
Method. You can be so immersed in a character,
that you've become that character. You believe

215
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:25,750
it all to be happening.

216
00:26:25,750 --> 00:26:31,630
If, that can be achieved by mundane actors,
then, what to speak of the eternally liberated

217
00:26:31,630 --> 00:26:41,169
associates of the Lord, under the influence
of Yoga-māyā. So, it's a level of intensity,

218
00:26:41,169 --> 00:26:51,640
and love, and affection, beyond what we can
conceive. It's not a light thing. So, when...

219
00:26:51,640 --> 00:26:55,100
it's heartbreaking to Nityānanda, but when
the devotees think of what it's going to do

220
00:26:55,100 --> 00:27:03,990
to Śacī-mātā and Viṣṇu Priya. They're...
it... they can't digest that... it's just

221
00:27:03,990 --> 00:27:15,150
killing them. And, what we find, that... that
night comes —which was two nights ago—

222
00:27:15,150 --> 00:27:21,510
and, devotees, they all come... and like,
in the evening visit Nimaī Paṇḍit.

223
00:27:21,510 --> 00:27:35,570
He garlands them. He knows He's going; Nityānanda,
Gadādhar, one or two others, Śacī-mātā.

224
00:27:35,570 --> 00:27:44,340
But, those devotees do not know. But, it just
so happens —maybe, perhaps through internal

225
00:27:44,340 --> 00:27:53,750
inspiration— kholā-vecā Śrīdhar, he
comes. Mahāprabhu drank from his water pot

226
00:27:53,750 --> 00:28:01,240
after the first nām-saṅkīrtan, when He
was utterly exhausted and thirsty. That broken,

227
00:28:01,240 --> 00:28:06,830
busted, patched, rusted, water pot, that's
where He drank His water. And, they were,

228
00:28:06,830 --> 00:28:11,620
like, trying to keep it away from Him. And,
He was, like, drinking that water as if it

229
00:28:11,620 --> 00:28:18,049
was the ultimate nectarean substance, because,
it was the water from kholā-vecā Śrīdhar.

230
00:28:18,049 --> 00:28:26,570
So, he comes and brings this lāu, you know,
gourd: pumpkin-like-gourd.

231
00:28:26,570 --> 00:28:37,140
And, Nimaī Paṇḍit saying, “How can
I not honor this before I go?” Someone else

232
00:28:37,140 --> 00:28:40,900
came and brought some milk, and then he told
Śacī-mātā, “Make something.” So, that's

233
00:28:40,900 --> 00:28:48,600
the last thing that He took before taking
sannyās. And then, that night, for some time

234
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:59,570
He entered yoga-nidrā. And Mother Śacī
knowing that He's leaving, she placed herself

235
00:28:59,570 --> 00:29:12,070
in the doorway, just out of utter desperation.
And then, at around 3 o'clock in the morning,

236
00:29:12,070 --> 00:29:21,980
He awoke. And, when He saw her, He bowed down
before her, “This body belongs to you mother.”

237
00:29:21,980 --> 00:29:22,980
And...

238
00:29:22,980 --> 00:29:35,780
But, to assuage her heartbreak, He saying,
“You are my mother eternally. In Rām-līlā

239
00:29:35,780 --> 00:29:43,730
you are my mother. In every kind of līlā
imaginable, you're always my mother. In Kṛṣṇa-līlā

240
00:29:43,730 --> 00:29:50,090
you're Yaśodā. In all these other Avatārs—
that is you. You're always my mother, eternally

241
00:29:50,090 --> 00:29:59,510
and forever.” Still, it's unbearable, heartbreak
for her —and He leaves. We know, He swims

242
00:29:59,510 --> 00:30:13,100
across the Gaṅgā and goes to Katwa to the
āśram —Keśava Bhāratī Mahārāj's—

243
00:30:13,100 --> 00:30:23,340
and, approaches him for sannyās. And, He's
saying that, “You can give me kṛṣṇa-bhakti.

244
00:30:23,340 --> 00:30:28,180
That's what I've come for. I want devotion
to Kṛṣṇa, you can give that.” And,

245
00:30:28,180 --> 00:30:40,710
Keśava Bhāratī's thinking, “This is kind
of absurd... But...” And, he's hesitant.

246
00:30:40,710 --> 00:30:45,380
We're told in the Bhāgavatam, with regard
to Viṣṇu Priya,

247
00:30:45,380 --> 00:30:52,070
tyaktvā su-dustyaja-surepsita-rājya-lakṣmīṁ
dharmiṣṭha ārya-vacasā yad agād araṇyam

248
00:30:52,070 --> 00:30:58,770
māyā-mṛgaṁ dayitayepsitam anvadhāvad
vande mahā-puruṣa te caraṇāravindam

249
00:30:58,770 --> 00:31:01,640
(Śrīmad Bhāgavatam: 11.5.34)

250
00:31:01,640 --> 00:31:07,770
This verse is interesting in the Bhāgavatam,
because it's equally applicable to Rāmacandra

251
00:31:07,770 --> 00:31:14,371
and Mahāprabhu, the vande mahā-puruṣa
te caraṇāravindam (SB: 11.5.34.4). When

252
00:31:14,371 --> 00:31:18,679
applied to Rāmacandra, it's saying, “He
gave up the imperial throne and together with

253
00:31:18,679 --> 00:31:25,880
Sītā and Lakṣmaṇ, they were exiled to
the forrest.” And, māyā-mṛgaṁ —the

254
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:31,120
Māyā took the form of a deer and deceived
Sītā. It's telling the rām-līlā in that

255
00:31:31,120 --> 00:31:40,549
way. Viśvanāth Cakravartī Ṭhākur applies
to Mahāprabhu, saying, tyaktvā su-dustyaja-surepsita-rājya-lakṣmīṁ

256
00:31:40,549 --> 00:31:45,740
(SB: 11.5.34.1). Rājya-lakṣmīṁ means
here, Viṣṇu Priya. He's saying, “He

257
00:31:45,740 --> 00:31:53,510
gave up the imperial throne of the love that's
in her heart.” That's what the imperial

258
00:31:53,510 --> 00:31:58,480
throne is—there. The love and the heart
of Viṣṇu Priya, which, is inconceivable

259
00:31:58,480 --> 00:32:02,630
to us. That He had to forgo.

260
00:32:02,630 --> 00:32:10,090
Why, māyā-mṛgaṁ dayitayepsitam anvadhāvad
(SB: 11.5.34.3), to chase after those souls

261
00:32:10,090 --> 00:32:15,970
who are running after Māyā. We're running,
we're deluded by māyā... we're running after

262
00:32:15,970 --> 00:32:25,340
Māyā's illusion. He's chasing after us to
rescue us. To do that, He had to leave the

263
00:32:25,340 --> 00:32:33,250
imperial throne and enshrined in the heart
of Viṣṇu Devī. So, He's there in Katwa

264
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:42,820
and the word has spread. Sometimes, people
begin to lament, who had offended Him. And,

265
00:32:42,820 --> 00:32:53,240
now we've driven Him out of Nadīyā, Navadwip,
nadīyā-dhārā kore gaura- jaya re. Guru

266
00:32:53,240 --> 00:33:00,240
Mahārāj would sing that, [Goswāmī Mahārāj
singing: nadīyā-dhārā kore gaura- jaya

267
00:33:00,240 --> 00:33:01,240
re].

268
00:33:01,240 --> 00:33:08,400
They're saying, “Oh, the light of Navadwip,
Nadīyā is gone, what have we done.” They're

269
00:33:08,400 --> 00:33:18,030
lamenting. See, already the transformation
is occurring. And, when He comes... Keśava

270
00:33:18,030 --> 00:33:26,260
Bhāratī, it appears, as though, the sun
is entering his āṣram. The effulgence of

271
00:33:26,260 --> 00:33:34,909
Mahāprabhu is so great. And then, he sees
this beautiful 24 year old young man, and

272
00:33:34,909 --> 00:33:39,630
He want to take sannyās, and he's thinking,
“This isn't good, this is not right.”

273
00:33:39,630 --> 00:33:48,419
Usually, in the Ved... dharmā, ārtha, kāma,
mokṣā, you know, at a later stage. When

274
00:33:48,419 --> 00:33:57,820
life, the life cycle, gṛhastha is finished
in the mid 50s or so, then sannyās. But,

275
00:33:57,820 --> 00:34:04,470
here at 24, and such a beautiful, extraordinarily,
inconceivably, beautiful young man.

276
00:34:04,470 --> 00:34:10,659
And, then people are threatening outside,
they're going, “Bhāratī, if you give sannyās

277
00:34:10,659 --> 00:34:17,040
we're going destroy your āśram. Who do you
think you are?” And, we're told, there're

278
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:23,210
some ladies going, “Who invented this sannyās
anyway? Where does this come from? Who came

279
00:34:23,210 --> 00:34:31,460
up with this idea? That a man, he should leave
his mother and family, what... this is crazy.

280
00:34:31,460 --> 00:34:38,330
Where does... who started this?” They're
all... and the crowd growing... and Keś...

281
00:34:38,330 --> 00:34:43,389
he's thinking how to get out of this. And,
he thinks, “Then, you have to go home and

282
00:34:43,389 --> 00:34:49,810
get your mother's permission.” I mean, it's
India after all. [chuckling] What was I saying?

283
00:34:49,810 --> 00:34:55,450
Then, He starts running and then Keśava Bhāratī
saying, like, “He's so charming, He's so

284
00:34:55,450 --> 00:35:00,600
beautiful, of course, He will convince...
tell Him to come back. Of course, He'll get

285
00:35:00,600 --> 00:35:04,250
permission. Who could refuse Him anything?”

286
00:35:04,250 --> 00:35:11,760
And, they bring Him back. Then, it's time
for the barber. And, that's the part where

287
00:35:11,760 --> 00:35:19,740
the devotees... they... He's so beautiful
with his hair. You know, His hair's long and

288
00:35:19,740 --> 00:35:29,790
it's perfumed, oiled, like, very nice —and
this they can't tolerate. And, His face is

289
00:35:29,790 --> 00:35:38,940
so beautiful, moon-like face, lotus eyes,
curling hair, it's just... they can't... And,

290
00:35:38,940 --> 00:35:46,470
the barber, he's hesitating; no one wants
to do this. They're trying to delay, find

291
00:35:46,470 --> 00:35:57,210
excuses to delay this. Nityānanda can't tolerate
it. No one wants this. And, somehow the day

292
00:35:57,210 --> 00:36:06,880
drags on and on and on, then it's arranged
that they will, the barber will shave His

293
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:07,880
hair.

294
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:15,860
And, then... and, Guru Mahārāj has recorded
this in his Premadhāma-deva-stotram, the

295
00:36:15,860 --> 00:36:24,150
lakṣa-lakṣa-koṭi... Tears from the eyes
