298
00:36:41,390 --> 00:36:47,890
How could I?” And Guru Mahārāj said, “He
later took the occupation of a sweet maker.”

299
00:36:47,890 --> 00:36:58,510
And, it was said, his sweets had some extraordinary
sweetness to them. Having touched sweetness

300
00:36:58,510 --> 00:37:05,640
personified, the cintāmaṇi touch of sweetness
personified, when he made sweets, they had

301
00:37:05,640 --> 00:37:11,359
extraordinary quality and characteristic.

302
00:37:11,359 --> 00:37:24,820
Then he's... who was it?.. Candraśekhara
Ācārya was assigned as His, like surrogate

303
00:37:24,820 --> 00:37:32,251
to do the rituals of sannyās. He didn't do
anything. Candraśekhar did everything, as

304
00:37:32,251 --> 00:37:42,320
a proxy. And, we're told repeatedly, when
they tried to to the ceremony repeatedly,

305
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:49,010
He will get up and start madly taking kṛṣṇa-nām.
Then, Keśava Bhāratī starts chanting, they

306
00:37:49,010 --> 00:37:53,800
have a kīrtan, then they, like, try to calm
down and go on with the ceremony. And, it

307
00:37:53,800 --> 00:38:00,230
starts again and again. And, then the time
comes for the mantraṁ.

308
00:38:00,230 --> 00:38:10,010
And, right before Keśava Bhāratī is going
to say the sannyā mantraṁ to Him, Nimaī

309
00:38:10,010 --> 00:38:17,700
Paṇḍit said, “A sādhu came to me in
a dream, and, whispered this... mind mantraṁ.

310
00:38:17,700 --> 00:38:25,820
It this the mantra?” And... which we know,
is generally taken to be, 'tat tvam asi.'

311
00:38:25,820 --> 00:38:32,360
It's the māyāvādi... where they're saying,
you know, “You are... 'thou art that', you

312
00:38:32,360 --> 00:38:39,109
are that Brahmā, that ultimate substance.”
That's how they take it. But, when Nimaī

313
00:38:39,109 --> 00:38:44,790
Paṇḍit says this to Keśava Bhāratī,
He's in essence, initiating him with... he's

314
00:38:44,790 --> 00:38:54,740
giving the real actual meaning, “I am His,
I belong to Him.” That's another meaning,

315
00:38:54,740 --> 00:39:03,330
it's gopī-bhāv. Or, if we take even higher,
“You are mine” —is the type of gopī-bhāv

316
00:39:03,330 --> 00:39:05,849
of Rādhārāṇī and Her associates.

317
00:39:05,849 --> 00:39:13,390
So, Keśava Bhāratī says, like... now, he's
initiated by Nimaī Paṇḍit, and saying,

318
00:39:13,390 --> 00:39:18,280
“Yes, that is the mantra.” [chuckles]
You know... Then, He vibrates the mantraṁ,

319
00:39:18,280 --> 00:39:25,290
and He said... And, he's thinking, “What
name shall be given to Him?” And, there's

320
00:39:25,290 --> 00:39:34,040
a system for giving names —108. Śaṅkarācārya
picked 10 and used those out of the 108 for

321
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:41,630
his line. We generally use all 108. But he...
and there's some system, which kind will be

322
00:39:41,630 --> 00:39:48,410
given, in which combination. And, he's thinking,
“But, none of that applies to you.” And,

323
00:39:48,410 --> 00:39:54,400
he's saying, “Because, the world is forgetful
of Kṛṣṇa Consciousness. And, you have

324
00:39:54,400 --> 00:40:02,740
descended to distributed Kṛṣṇa Consciousness
to everyone.

325
00:40:02,740 --> 00:40:08,330
That means Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya. You have
descended, you are Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya,

326
00:40:08,330 --> 00:40:17,160
you are Kṛṣṇa Consciousness personified.
And your distributing Kṛṣṇa Consciousness

327
00:40:17,160 --> 00:40:27,660
to everyone. So, your name must be Śrī Kṛṣṇa
Chaitanya.” [laughing] And, everyone, “Jaya,

328
00:40:27,660 --> 00:40:35,631
Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya kī jaya!” And
who was it?.. Śrīnivāsa Ācārya's father

329
00:40:35,631 --> 00:40:44,290
was there at the time. And, when he heard
this 'Chaitanya,' he became half mad. And,

330
00:40:44,290 --> 00:40:49,930
wandered around going, “Chaitanya, Chaitanya,
Chaitanya!” And, when he went to his village,

331
00:40:49,930 --> 00:40:57,339
and everyone will say, “What happened in
Katwa?” “Chaitanya, Chaitanya, Chaitanya!”

332
00:40:57,339 --> 00:40:59,130
