Sridhar Dev-Goswāmī Mahārāj), with His...
general... His associates... generally to

487
00:58:16,829 --> 00:58:23,070
nām-saṅkīrtan, distributing krṣṇa-prem,
giving other entrance. But, what is His internal

488
00:58:23,070 --> 00:58:28,730
thing, antarangha sange-kore rasa-asvadan
(Śrīla Bhakti Raksak Sridhar Dev-Goswāmī

489
00:58:28,730 --> 00:58:37,040
Mahārāj), to taste rāsa. Who is rāsa?
Not just, what is rāsa. Whom? Rāsa-rāj

490
00:58:37,040 --> 00:58:44,210
is Kṛṣṇa. So, as Guru Mahāraj says,
“Sweetness is tasting itself.” Because,

491
00:58:44,210 --> 00:58:50,680
you see, everyone is mad after sweetness,
and sees the effects that sweetness has upon

492
00:58:50,680 --> 00:59:00,470
people. He thinks, “I want to experience
the same.” So, sweetness tasting itself,

493
00:59:00,470 --> 00:59:13,349
and becoming mad, as an outcome, expressed
in ecstatic dance and song. So, it's said,

494
00:59:13,349 --> 00:59:22,069
“The cause is the effect —the effect is
the cause.” ātma-siddha-sāvalīla-pūrṇa-saukhya-lakṣaṇaṁ

495
00:59:22,069 --> 00:59:31,830
(Pds: 66.1), the ultimate conception of the
ultimate reality is, He's singing and dancing.

496
00:59:31,830 --> 00:59:35,700
Why? On the account... if, He... Īśopaniṣads
say,

497
00:59:35,700 --> 00:59:40,210
oṁ pūrṇam adaḥ pūrṇam idaṁ
pūrṇāt pūrṇam udacyate

498
00:59:40,210 --> 00:59:43,030
pūrṇasya pūrṇam ādāya
pūrṇam evāvaśiṣyate

499
00:59:43,030 --> 00:59:44,160
(Īśopaniṣad: Invocation)

500
00:59:44,160 --> 00:59:51,809
So, it... pūrṇa, just doesn't mean 'full,'
like, you know, a glass is full. It also means;

501
00:59:51,809 --> 01:00:00,460
complete, fulfilled, utterly fulfilled, totally
fulfilled. That is the position of ecstasy

502
01:00:00,460 --> 01:00:09,720
personified. But, in this case, the Supreme-positive
is taking the position of the Supreme-negative.

503
01:00:09,720 --> 01:00:16,130
To relish... Kṛṣṇa relishing His own
name. Only, from the position of a devotee

504
01:00:16,130 --> 01:00:24,150
—can. As Kṛṣṇa —not. But, as a devotee
—and not only devotee— we're back to the

505
01:00:24,150 --> 01:00:32,180
voltage of the kṛṣṇa-nām of Rādhārāṇī.
With rādhā-bhāv, how tasteful is Kṛṣṇa.

506
01:00:32,180 --> 01:00:40,369
He's experiencing that. And, that is making
Him so happy and fulfilled. Like, in the true

507
01:00:40,369 --> 01:00:45,730
sense of the word —ecstatic— means beyond
yourself.

508
01:00:45,730 --> 01:00:53,380
He's besides Himself, beyond Himself. The
end result is it's expressed in ecstatic dance

509
01:00:53,380 --> 01:01:07,720
and singing of kṛṣṇa-nām, which is
the nām-saṅkīrtan movement. So, we're

510
01:01:07,720 --> 01:01:23,410
supremely fortunate, that on this day, Mahāprabhu,
He —despite the personal heartbreak involved,

511
01:01:23,410 --> 01:01:32,420
and it's something real and true. Mother Śacī,
Viṣṇu Priya Devī, and all the devotees,

512
01:01:32,420 --> 01:01:40,200
that to say —rescue all the fallen souls.
He did this. [clearing voice]

513
01:01:40,200 --> 01:01:50,240
So, it's the gift of Mother Śacī, Viṣṇu
Priya, Advaita Ācārya, Haridās Ṭhākur,

514
01:01:50,240 --> 01:02:02,220
all the great devotees. So, the... when I
asked Guru Mahāraj once, I said, “So, which

515
01:02:02,220 --> 01:02:12,460
shall we consider?,,” We see the depths
of rāḍhā-bhāv plunged in the pastimes

516
01:02:12,460 --> 01:02:19,740
in Purī. Particularly in the Gambhīrā,
behind closed doors with Svarūp Dāmodar

517
01:02:19,740 --> 01:02:26,010
and Rāmānanda. So, then I thought, “But,
then... what about Navadwip. Which would be

518
01:02:26,010 --> 01:02:33,680
considered, you know, higher?” And, I'll
never forget. Guru Mahārāj said, “Stalwart

519
01:02:33,680 --> 01:02:40,230
followers of Mahāprabhu prefer Navadwip.”
[laughing]

520
01:02:40,230 --> 01:02:47,099
And, then I could understand. So, it... from
one point of view, we'll say, “The depths

521
01:02:47,099 --> 01:02:53,400
of rādhā-bhāv are plunged behind closed
doors in Purī.” But, all of this does not

522
01:02:53,400 --> 01:03:02,869
make the devotees happy. To see the beautiful
locks of Nimaī shorn away, when He takes

523
01:03:02,869 --> 01:03:10,609
sannyās. The results of those ecstatic symptoms,
it's giving some pain in their hearts. They

524
01:03:10,609 --> 01:03:16,910
only... they want these happy pastimes like
they had in Navadwip. That's the 'good old

525
01:03:16,910 --> 01:03:24,950
days' for them. So, he said, “Stalwart followers
of Mahāprabhu, they prefer Navadwip.” And,

526
01:03:24,950 --> 01:03:31,349
then the evidence of Bhaktivinod Ṭhākur
given in that song, When Will He Join Us Again.

527
01:03:31,349 --> 01:03:39,200
So, all these thing have to be considered
very carefully.

528
01:03:39,200 --> 01:03:49,930
But, at the heart of the matter, is union
in separation. As, Guru Mahārāj... “Necessity

529
01:03:49,930 --> 01:03:56,670
indicates separation.” This is his point.
We have some particular necessity. Necessity,

530
01:03:56,670 --> 01:04:05,720
and it means, we don't have that thing. So,
in that sense, we're separated. And, we know,

531
01:04:05,720 --> 01:04:13,740
hunger produces relish. When you're really
hungry, then you really enjoy... that's when

532
01:04:13,740 --> 01:04:24,440
you enjoy eat... every morsel is just wonderful.
Like the saying, 'hunger is the best spice.'

533
01:04:24,440 --> 01:04:30,850
It's that principle that's... and... and,
thankfully, mercifully, this is something

534
01:04:30,850 --> 01:04:40,400
that's realistic for us to culture. For neophytes,
to try and cultivate pastimes of union, is

535
01:04:40,400 --> 01:04:45,150
not realistic, it's inappropriate, and it's
damaging.

536
01:04:45,150 --> 01:04:56,299
Because, we can't see beyond our senses and
mundane sensuality, at this point. So, we'll

537
01:04:56,299 --> 01:05:05,309
make the grave mistake of imposing mundane
sensuality upon, the objective world, upon

538
01:05:05,309 --> 01:05:16,770
the super subjective sensuality of the aprākṛta-līlā
of Kṛṣṇa. That's a grave mistake. But,

539
01:05:16,770 --> 01:05:23,720
we see the highest, the greatest depths of
kṛṣṇa-prem are mined from the position

540
01:05:23,720 --> 01:05:28,369
of separation, bāhye viṣa-jvālā haya,
bhitare ānanda-maya, kṛṣṇa-premāra

541
01:05:28,369 --> 01:05:33,240
adbhuta carita (Cc: Madhya-līlā, 2.50.3-4).
And, this is a subject matter of Chaitanya-charitāmṛtam.

542
01:05:33,240 --> 01:05:40,589
As, Gurudev said, “What is Mahāprabu's
tasting matter?” It's tasting what you feel

543
01:05:40,589 --> 01:05:42,670
in separation.

544
01:05:42,670 --> 01:05:48,210
It's achieved the deeper region of heart.
Therefore, a deeper type of love and more

545
01:05:48,210 --> 01:05:56,350
tasteful. A deeper sort of relish. And, that
is... this is supreme mercy, in that. That's

546
01:05:56,350 --> 01:06:03,510
the position that is realistic for us. Because,
if one thing we know, we are separated from

547
01:06:03,510 --> 01:06:11,299
Kṛṣṇa. So, that's the only legitimate
sort of culture for us. But, it happens to

548
01:06:11,299 --> 01:06:19,020
yield the very highest things. So, how fortunate
we are. And, Mahāprabhu has come demonstrating

549
01:06:19,020 --> 01:06:32,910
this, in His pastimes. Hare Kṛṣṇa. [clapping
hands] Śrī Kṛṣṇa Chaitanya Mahāprabhu's

550
01:06:32,910 --> 01:06:36,420
sannyāsa-līlā smaraṇam ki! jay!

551
01:06:36,420 --> 01:06:37,420
Jay!

552
01:06:37,420 --> 01:06:46,579
Hare Kṛṣṇa. And, that's why the devotees
don't like to see that... they... so, we worship

553
01:06:46,579 --> 01:06:55,069
Mahāprabhu, not with a shaved head. But,
looking like Nimaī Paṇḍit. [laughing]

